                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d490">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.30/218: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-11-20T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 20, 1930—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>90. Your 153, November 18, 3 p.m. Please see telegram 1019 sent by Navy
                    Department to Admiral Irwin yesterday. This Department concurs in views
                    expressed therein.</p>
                <p>Ascertain informally and as early as practicable the views of the <pb facs="0538"
                        n="458" xml:id="pg_458"/> Brazilian authorities and the Chief of the Naval
                    Mission with regard to the time necessary to permit the closing of official and
                    personal business of the Mission and submit your personal recommendations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
